timemanager

Class TimerDisplay

  • java.lang.Object
    • timemanager.TimerDisplay

  • public class TimerDisplay
extends java.lang.Object
    UI for the actual timer, TM_Timer. Write entries into log file upon reset or removal. TimerEntry in log: time stamp, hours, minutes, seconds, custom note

    • Method Detail

      • getVBox

        public javafx.scene.layout.VBox getVBox()

      • startBtnClicked

        public void startBtnClicked()
        startButton handler. If button text on click is: - Start: Save initial timer data, disable UI, start the timer - Pause: Stop the timer, enable UI, save current timer data - Continue: Start timer from current state, disable UI - Done: Stop alarm sound, reset timer

      • resetClicked

        public void resetClicked()
        resetBtn handler. If "save" is checked, create entry in log file. Restore comboboxes to intial values and enable UI.

      • removeClicked

        public void removeClicked()
        removeBtn handler. If "save" is checked, create entry in log file. Remove the timer from the UI and the timers list.

      • saveEntry

        private void saveEntry()
        saveBtn handler. If intial data is not null, meaning that the timer has been used, then create an entry in the log file and send feedback to UI.
